value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: trans-cyclohexane-1,2-diol + NAD+ = 2-hydroxycyclohexan-1-one + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: cyclohexane-1,3-dione + H2O = 5-oxohexanoate + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: A + cyclohexanone = AH(2) + cyclohex-2-enone.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + cyclomaltodextrin = linear maltodextrin.
Catalysis of the reaction: cyclopentanone + H+ + NADPH + O2 = 5-valerolactone + H2O + NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction: cysteamine + O2 = H+ + hypotaurine.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-cysteine + 2-oxoglutarate = mercaptopyruvate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + S-(4-bromophenyl)-L-cysteine = (4-bromophenylsulfanyl)pyruvate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction: L-cysteine + sulfite = L-cysteate + sulfide.
Catalysis of the reaction: S-substituted L-cysteine + H2O = a thiol + NH4+ + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: CTP = 3',5'-cyclic CMP + diphosphate + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2 H2 + ferricytochrome c3 = 4 H+ + ferrocytochrome c3.
Catalysis of the reaction: 6-alkylaminopurine + UDP-D-glucose = 6-alkylamino-7-beta-D-glucosylpurine + H+ + UDP. This reaction is an N-glucosylation event.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-tartrate = H2O + oxaloacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-lactate + A = AH(2) + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-alanine + 2-oxoglutarate = pyruvate + D-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-alanine + L-glutamine = gamma-L-glutamyl-D-alanine + NH4.
Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + a D-amino acid = CoA + an N-acetyl-D-amino-acid.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-arabinitol + NAD+ = D-xylulose + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-arabinose + ATP = D-arabinose 5-phosphate + ADP.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-arabinono-1,4-lactone + H2O = D-arabinonate + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-arabinose + NAD+ = D-arabinono-1,4-lactone + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-arginine + H2O = D-ornithine + urea.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-fuconate = 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-fuconate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-glutamate + H2O + O2 = 2-oxoglutarate + NH3 + H2O2, and D-aspartate + H2O + O2 = oxaloacetate + NH3 + H2O2.

definition.value: For the individual reactions, see instead 'D-glutamate oxidase activity ;GO:0047821' and 'D-aspartate oxidase activity ; GO:0008445'.

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glutamate = 5-oxo-D-proline + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-glutamate + H2O + O2 = 2-oxoglutarate + H2O2 + NH4+.
Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + hypotaurine + NADPH + O2 = H2O + NADP+ + taurine.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-glutamate + D-glutamine = gamma-D-glutamyl-D-glutamate + NH4+. Can also transfer additional glutamyl residues to a peptide, extending the polypeptide chain.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-iditol + NAD+ = D-sorbose + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-2-O-sulfolactate + H2O = (R)-lactate + H+ + sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-lysine = (2R,5S)-2,5-diaminohexanoate and (3S)-3,6-diaminohexanoate = (3S,5S)-3,5-diaminohexanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-lysopine + H2O + NADP+ = L-lysine + H+ + NADPH + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-lyxose = D-xylulose.
Catalysis of the reaction: N2-(D-1,3-dicarboxypropyl)-L-arginine + NADP+ + H2O = L-arginine + 2-oxoglutarate + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction: N2-(D-1-carboxyethyl)-L-arginine + NAD+ + H2O = L-arginine + pyruvate + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-ornithine = (2R,4S)-2,4-diaminopentanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 5D-5-O-methyl-chiro-inositol + NADP+ = 2D-5-O-methyl-2,3,5/4,6-pentahydroxycyclohexanone + H+ + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-sorbitol + acceptor = L-sorbose + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: a D-threo-aldose + NAD+ = a D-threo-aldono-1,5-lactone + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-tryptophan + acetyl-CoA = N-acetyl-D-tryptophan + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-tryptophan + malonyl-CoA = N(2)-malonyl-D-tryptophan + CoA + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-xylose + NADP+ = D-xylono-1,5-lactone + H+ + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction: D-xylose + NAD+ = D-xylonolactone + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction: dATP + depurinated DNA = ribose triphosphate + DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction: dCTP + H2O = dCMP + H+ + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-dehydro-D-gluconate + ATP = 6-phospho-2-dehydro-D-gluconate + ADP + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction: 3-dehydro-L-gulonate + H+ = L-xylulose + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-dehydro-D-gluconate + A = 2,5-didehydro-D-gluconate + AH(2).
Catalysis of the reaction: deoxylimonoate + H2O = deoxylimononate D-ring-lactone + H+.
